# Plan: Live Data, Modals, and Better Error Handling

We will transform the remaining hardcoded sections of the Pomelo platform into a fully dynamic application. This includes replacing native alerts with custom modals, connecting the User Dashboard to the backend, and cleaning up all mock "test" data.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Dashboard Data**: The dashboard will now reflect the *real* user's bookings. If a new user logs in, the dashboard will appear empty (as it should) instead of showing the hardcoded "Olena Dyachenko" data.
> - **Modal System**: We are building a custom Modal component. This will change the look and feel of error messages and confirmations compared to native browser boxes.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Backend Integration

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/Кирилл/Documents/Проекты/pomelo/backend/main.py)
- Create `@app.get("/bookings/me")` endpoint to return a list of bookings for the current authenticated user.
- Ensure the booking includes related `Tour` information.

### 2. Frontend Infrastructure

#### [NEW] [Modal.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Кирилл/Documents/Проекты/pomelo/frontend/src/components/common/Modal.tsx)
- Create a reusable, styled Modal component with a backdrop and smooth animations.

#### [NEW] [Modal.css](file:///c:/Users/Кирилл/Documents/Проекты/pomelo/frontend/src/components/common/Modal.css)
- Implement premium glassmorphism styles for the modal.

### 3. Page Refactoring

#### [MODIFY] [DashboardPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Кирилл/Documents/Проекты/pomelo/frontend/src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx)
- Integrate `AuthContext` to display the real user's name, email, and avatar initials.
- Fetch real bookings from `/bookings/me`.
- Replace hardcoded cards with a loop that renders live booking data.
- Handle the "Empty State" (no bookings yet) with a beautiful "Find your first tour" CTA.

#### [MODIFY] [AuthPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Кирилл/Documents/Проекты/pomelo/frontend/src/pages/AuthPage.tsx)
- Improve the error display logic.
- Replace any remaining native `alert()` calls with the new `Modal` component.

#### [MODIFY] [AdminPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Кирилл/Documents/Проекты/pomelo/frontend/src/pages/AdminPage.tsx)
- Ensure the "Stats" section (total bookings, revenue) uses live data from the database where possible.

## Open Questions

- Should I implement a "Profile Update" feature right now (since it's on the dashboard), or just make sure the name/email are displayed correctly from the current session?

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Browser test: Log in with a fresh admin account and verify the dashboard is clean and shows the correct name.
- Browser test: Trigger an error (invalid login) and verify it appears in a styled UI element/modal instead of a native alert.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that "Olena Dyachenko" is no longer visible anywhere in the app.
